            "id": "56daccf59fa848de8d8e5",
            "questionText": "A white light source is incident on a diffraction grating with 600 lines per millimeter. The resulting spectrum is projected onto a screen 2 meters away from the grating. Calculate the linear separation ($!$\\Delta y$!$) between the red light ($!$\\lambda = 700$!$ nm) and the blue light ($!$\\lambda = 400$!$ nm) in the first-order spectrum (n = 1), assuming the grating equation $!$d \\sin(\\theta) = n\\lambda$!$ and the small angle approximation where applicable.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "72875d2fecfe4807a8641",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by determining the grating spacing ($!$d$!$) based on the line density given. Please select the correct relation for calculating $!$d$!$ from the number of lines per meter.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "15cf7c79-9158-42b2-b21a-603d53e13a58"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$ d = \\frac{1}{\\text{lines per meter}} $!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$ d = \\text{lines per meter} $!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$ d = \\text{lines per millimeter} \\times 1000 $!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "a3e6878c83104beb88a3e",
                    "stepText": "Great! Now, to find the diffraction angles for each wavelength, we need to use the grating equation in combination with the small angle approximation. Please choose the correct grating equation that relates $!$d$, $!$\\theta$!$, $!$n$!$, and $!$\\lambda$!$.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "15cf7c79-9158-42b2-b21a-603d53e13a58"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$ d\\sin\\theta = n\\lambda $!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$ d\\theta = n\\lambda $!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$ \\sin\\theta = \\frac{d}{n\\lambda} $!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "b9aace4f6ed041038473b",
                    "stepText": "Now, using the small angle approximation, the diffraction angle can be approximated as $!$\\theta \\approx \\frac{\\lambda}{d}$!$. Calculate the difference between the diffraction angles for the red light ($!$\\lambda = 700 \\times 10^{-9}$!$ m) and the blue light ($!$\\lambda = 400 \\times 10^{-9}$!$ m). Provide the numerical value for $!$(\\theta_{red} - \\theta_{blue})$!$ in radians.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "0.18"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "rad",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "fccc17be-fcc2-4075-82c4-e570a95384e9"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "ba3149f6730444c297089",
                    "stepText": "Finally, with the angular difference obtained and knowing that the screen is placed 2 m away, calculate the linear separation ($!$\\Delta y$!$) on the screen using the small angle relation $!$y \\approx L\\theta$!$. Compute $!$\\Delta y = L(\\theta_{red} - \\theta_{blue})$!$ and provide the numeric value.",
